Assurant Says Storms May Cost Insurer as Much as $75 Million

-- B y   A n d r e w   F r y e
-- 
2011-06-02T12:58:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/assurant-says-storms-may-cost-insurer-as-much-as-75-million.html
Assurant Inc. (AIZ) , the insurer of
foreclosed properties, said catastrophes in April and May
probably will cost the company about $65 million to $75 million.  The losses are from hail, tornadoes, wind and flooding, the
New York-based insurer said today in a regulatory filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Frye in New York at 
 afrye@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  